Welcome back from summer!
We hope you’re feeling recharged, because we are!

This Fall 2025, we’re kicking off a brand new cohort at HighTechXL. 

Our scouting team ( shoutout to Earl Goetheer and Deepika Poonia 🙌 )  has been hard at work finding breakthrough technologies from research institutes and labs worldwide. And let’s just say… the tech coming into this cohort is seriously exciting. 

We’ll be sharing the first one tomorrow 👀

In the meantime, we’ve also refreshed how we tell our story: check out our brand new website ✨

🔎 If you’ve ever asked yourself, “What would it be like to build a deep-tech venture from scratch?” this is your moment. Our selection process is open now, and we’re on the lookout for ambitious co-founders to join the journey.

👉 Check out the “Come a Founder” page, explore the process, and apply via the form: https://lnkd.in/dkVr3xQh

Help us spread the word, your network might know the next founder!

recent_posts.text:
And just before the summer season, the ASML talents completed their journey into deep-tech entrepreneurship.

Over the past three months, a new cohort of ASML professionals stepped out of their day-to-day roles and into the fast-moving world of early-stage startups at HighTechXL.

For 1.5 days a week, talents joined forces with deep-tech ventures tackling some of the world’s toughest challenges.

💡 Talents brought their technical depth and sharp thinking.
 🔥 Startups offered a fresh perspective, experimentation, and real-world impact.

Along the way, some talents became more proactive, taking initiative, speaking up, and pursuing their own ambitions without waiting for permission. 

Others learned how to delegate more effectively, communicate with clarity and purpose, and align better with the needs of their audience. A few discovered the value of taking a calculated risk now and then. 

Big thanks to the ventures who welcomed this year’s talents and to the mentors who guided them along the way.

#DeepTech #StartupExperience #ASMLTalentProgram #EntrepreneurialGrowth #HighTechXL

recent_posts.text:
Deep tech is hard. Progress is earned.
5 ventures just proved what’s possible.

At HighTechXL, we build deep-tech ventures from the ground up.
﻿And behind each venture?
Researchers, co-founders, and tech partners who refused to settle.

Each step is earned, and we’re proud to share a new milestone as 5 teams have passed their program gates. 
Some validated their business cases.
Others are already building early prototypes.

What’s moving forward?
🔹 Biobatteries – Building sustainable battery solutions for a cleaner future
🔹 AutomatED – Accelerating electron microscopy
🔹 Entonome – Making complex processes autonomous, faster, and more efficient
🔹 HighTechBinders – Revolutionizing asphalt with bio-based materials
🔹Galuxea - Creating eco-friendly antifouling solutions, using integrated low emission UVC light

These aren’t just promising ideas. They’re real solutions to real-world challenges.

Special thanks to the tech transfer heroes and institutions who believe in impact as much as invention, including TNO, Forschungszentrum Jülich, University of Antwerp, VBTI, PhotonFirst and Philips. Let’s keep pushing.

👀 Eyes on the horizon. More gates to come.

#DeepTech #VentureBuilding #Innovation #HighTechXL #StartupJourney #TechTransfer #XLDay

recent_posts.text:
What a day.
What a community.

Last year, we asked you to think big, right here at home.
And at XL Day 2025, we saw what that looks like in action.

With the amazing Robin van Scheijndel leading the day, we went from the rollercoaster stories of Dr. Hamed Sadeghian, CEO of Nearfield Instruments  Instruments, and Hans De Neve, CEO of Carbyon, to the incredible pitches by our latest cohort of ventures, alumni, Singapore teams, and ASML talents.

Each moment reminded us why we do this. Building in deep tech isn’t easy. But with collaboration, perseverance, and a little irrational optimism, it’s possible.

A special thanks to the teams who worked hard to be on stage: @High Tech Binders, Galuxea, @Ovalytix, Veridis, Luper Technologies, SonicPrecision, Ailytics, N&E Innovations Pte Ltd, WO:EX Pte Ltd., Gray Matter Solutions.

In the second part of the afternoon, we had three amazing breakout sessions led by Frank Smallegange, guiding us through the Hero’s Journey; Patricia de Kort, Soukaina Adnane-Murphy, and Michael Stucky, challenging the ventures in the Investors’ Arena; and Luis Pedro Oliveira, H. C.  (Hugo) Leyte, Stefan Kuipers, Aron Vromans, and John Bell leading an interactive panel on SecurityXL.

Right here in this region, we’re growing a powerhouse. Powered by founders. Backed by brave investors and partners. But we’re just getting started.

We’re filled with gratitude for everyone who joined, shared, pitched, supported, and simply showed up with open minds and big dreams. Thank you. 💙

Were you there? We’d love to hear:
 👉 What moved you?
 👉 What stuck with you?
 👉 What surprised or inspired you?

Drop your thoughts in the comments,  we’d love to hear what you took away from the day.

Read the full article by IO+ NL: https://lnkd.in/eG364qy9

#XLDay2025 #DeepTech #HighTechXL #VentureBuilding #Gratitude #InnovationEcosystem

Joris Jansens, Esther Peeks, Ximena C., Letícia Batista, Earl Goetheer, Ivana Pomazi, Deepika Poonia, High Tech Campus Eindhoven
